Cody continued toward the opening. To his right, Lulu paced him, trotting alongside with an alert air. Absently, Cody
reached down to stroke her head as they walked. As his hand drew close, Cody realized what he was doing, and snatched his
hand back as if burned. “Maybe a little too soon for that,” he said, eyeing the little dog. Lulu twitched an ear, but
otherwise did not react.
